raw.title: Saunagus Session.
raw.description:
Saturday 28 June 2025
20:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat for three rounds of ‘Saunagus’, a unique experience that combines heat, essential oils and music alongside your sauna experience.
By trained ‘gus master’ Oliver, he will deliver this traditional Danish ritual by using towel-swinging techniques to disperse the hot steam rhythmically to the music in every 15-minute long session.
Pure, organic essential oils compressed in ice balls placed on the sauna’s stove slowly disperses an aromatic steam which enhances the health properties of the experience.
Different essential oils can be utilised for different outcomes. For instance, peppermint can be used as a revitalising oil, lavender for calm and eucalyptus to clear the airways.
Each week the sessions will be themed through the scent of the essential oils, the music and movement to create a stimulating, relaxing or detoxifying effect on your body.
The ritual will leave you feeling both mentally and physically revived. Benefits range from a meditative state of mind to improving cardiovascular strength, boosting the immune system, as well as alleviating pain.
Sweheat it out.

Step into a slow, sensory evening rooted in the ancestral sauna traditions of the Baltic lands - led by Silvija, founder of Birch House Rituals.
This ritual draws on her Lithuanian heritage, weaving together the wisdom of the Pirtis with herbal medicine, folklore and plant spirit. Guided by the rhythms of the season and the healing power of trees and wild plants, you’ll be invited to soften, release, and return to presence.
Held in the warmth of the sauna, aromatic steam mingles with wild-foraged salt scrubs, raw honey, and hand-crafted whisks to create a space of deep restoration and reconnection.
Rooted in tree energetics, infused with plant essences, and dusted with whispers of Baltic amber, this is a body prayer - a communion with the wisdom of the Earth.
Expect:
Guided Lithuanian Pirtis ritual
Handmade herbal salt scrubs + raw honey facials
Halotherapy + aromatic steam
Plant-whisking and seasonal energetics
Subtle ritual elements rooted in Baltic nature

20:00 22:00

Join us at Sweheat for a two-hour Simply Aufguss session with Kyle Buttner.
Aufguss rituals – hallmarks of the European sauna experience – feature a sauna master guiding you through 15-minute sessions of heat, aromas, music, and special towel-waving techniques that circulate the air for a perfect sauna experience. During the Aufguss session, you’ll take part in three distinct rituals, ranging from traditional heat infusions to banya-inspired techniques. Between rituals, take some time to sit back and cool off in the winter air, maybe even taking a dip in the cold plunge. Each ritual is thoughtfully crafted to relax, invigorate, and entertain, so it's a fun and refreshing way to spend your evening.
Whether you’re looking to unwind after a busy week, gearing up for a night out, or searching for a unique activity to enjoy with friends, Aufguss is the perfect choice. It’s designed for everyone—seasoned sauna-goers, first-timers, groups, and individuals are all welcome.
Spaces are limited, so book now!

raw.title: Rekindling - Sauna Social and Supper Club.
raw.description:
Thursday 25 September 2025
18:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat Sauna for a supper club and social as we enjoy the rare opportunity to enjoy Rekindling - fire art installation from the warmth and comfort of our Sauna spaces.
French fire alchemists, Compagnie Carabosse and Royal Docks communities combine to create Rekindling, an evocative fire installation on land and water. Rekindling explores the metamorphosis of the Royal Docks. Built during the Industrial Revolution as the largest enclosed docks in the world, Royal Docks aided London’s growth as a global city. Now the area is reemerging as a centre for enterprise, innovation and culture powered by its diverse communities, pioneering spirit, and global links.
One of France’s most important street arts groups, Compagnie Carabosse have delighted thousands of visitors across the world with their work. The installation will make best use of the reflective surfaces of London City Hall and the Dock side water scape, making the atmosphere of this area come alive with its elemental nature.
Sweheat will provide access to both Saunas, fire pit, BBQ area and hot Jacket Potatoes.
Bring your own fillings and alcoholic beverages to be enjoyed throughout the evening as we wander through the art installation together or alone. Coming back to Sweheat for a perfect sweat and social time.

raw.title: Sparkling Sauna - Lithuanian Sauna Ritual.
raw.description:
18:00 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
“Ivan Beats The Gong” together with “Sweheat Sauna” invites you to a special sauna evening in London.
The ritual will be guided by sauna master Silvija, who is a herbalist and founder of Birch House Rituals. She carries Lithuanian plant and sauna traditions, inviting people to reconnect with nature and themselves.
The ritual is going to take participants on a four-stage journey: starting with a gentle introduction to the heat, followed by salt therapy and whisking, then a refreshing shower of sparkling mineral water, and finally a calming mask to close the evening.
It’s an experience where heat, aromas, and natural elements come together to open up a whole new dimension of the sauna.
Only 20 spots available, hurry up to register!
Round 1 – Gentle introduction to heat
The evening begins softly: mild temperature, deep breathing, essential oils, and the cooling flow of fans help the body settle. A sip of mineral water refreshes from within as the body gets acquainted with the warmth.
Round 2 – Salt therapy
Salt particles spread through the sauna – breathing becomes clearer, the skin softer, and circulation more active. A magnesium salt massage on the skin revitalizes, while mineral water helps restore balance.
Round 3 – Whisking and a refreshing full-body experience
The heat intensifies. Whisks and compresses embrace the whole body, while slowly poured sparkling mineral water over the head creates a light tingling sensation and a refreshing release.
Round 4 – Farewell to the heat
A short and concentrated finale. A nourishing face mask made of honey, oil, and mineral water soothes the skin. The ritual closes with one last pour of mineral water and a calm return to presence.
Event dates: October 23 & 24, 18:00 – 21:00
Open to men and women.

19:00 21:30
Google Calendar ICS
Step into a deliciously dark fairytale this Halloween, where scented steam, candlelight, and ancient stories entwine. Join us for an immersive Mythic Sauna experience — a night of storytelling, ritual, and wonder as we honour the turning of the seasons.
Woven through four sauna sessions, expert storyteller Oliver Wallace will tell a chilling fairytale from the deep mythic roots of northern Europe. Between sessions we will cold plunge, sip wild-foraged tea, and share pumpkin soup around the fire as we prepare for the longer nights ahead.
As the nights draw in and the veil between worlds thins, we gather in community to meet the dark — and remember that warmth, laughter, and story can carry us safely through it.
“It completely exceeded my expectations. Oliver’s storytelling captivated and inspired me.”
“It’s like coming out of the world out there, into this little oasis of peace and connection” “It was amazing to have so much presence with all the body sensations - with the heat, the scents, the cold, and the images that were forming.”
Find out about Oliver: www.linktr.ee/oliverwallacestories .

raw.title: Traditional Lithuanian Pirtis Ritual with Birch House Rituals.
raw.description:
Saturday 6 December 2025
18:00 20:00
Google Calendar ICS
Step into a slow, sensory evening rooted in the ancestral sauna traditions of the Baltic lands - led by Silvija, founder of Birch House Rituals.
This ritual draws on her Lithuanian heritage, weaving together the wisdom of the Pirtis with herbal medicine, folklore and plant spirit. Guided by the rhythms of the season and the healing power of trees and wild plants, you’ll be invited to soften, release, and return to presence.
Held in the warmth of the sauna, aromatic steam mingles with wild-foraged salt scrubs, raw honey, and hand-crafted whisks to create a space of deep restoration and reconnection.
Rooted in tree energetics, infused with plant essences, and dusted with whispers of Baltic amber, this is a body prayer - a communion with the wisdom of the Earth.
Expect:
Guided Lithuanian Pirtis ritual
Handmade herbal salt scrubs + raw honey facials
Halotherapy + aromatic steam
Plant-whisking and seasonal energetics
Subtle ritual elements rooted in Baltic nature

raw.title: Let’s Glow - NYE Party
raw.description:
Wednesday 31 December 2025 20:00 Thursday 1 January 2026 01:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us as we say goodbye to 2025 with our second Neon, New Years Eve celebration at Sweheat sauna.
Wear your best NEON glow sauna wear and we will provide the body paints and glow sticks.
Joining us this year will be two of the UKs best Sauna Masters, Oliver from Saunagus UK and Wendy Liu from Saunawave.
Both of our Saunas will be lit up with rituals and lights to create a perfect atmosphere to release the departing year and welcoming in the new. From leaf whisking to aromatherapy to ice infusions we will provide the right heat for a great evening.
You will be greeted at Sweheat Sauna with a hot Cacao drink to get the evening off to a fabulous start.
There will be music playing from our DJ Booth to get the party started, whilst we adorn the body with paints and good wishes for the new year. We will have an added extra space with a large Sauna Tent as our chill out zone for a less intense and social experience.
After some themed and theatrical Saunatainment from our fabulous Sauna Masters we will venture to the Dock side to watch the fireworks from the surrounding area.
We will wind down the evening with some more heat and time to socialise before dipping in the dock, bare if you dare just before we wrap up the evening.
There will be snacks and an area for BBQing so bring your bangers and something to share.
Cold drinks will be on sale but feel free to bring a bottle if you fancy something stronger for your celebrations.
More details to follow so be sure to sign up to our socials via Facebook or Instagram.

18:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us for a full evening of special aufguss rituals from top sauna masters, access to multiple saunas, and plenty of time and space to hang out and unwind.
Lange Saunanacht (German for “long sauna night”) is a full-evening sauna experience, our take on a common German sauna tradition.
We're bringing you:
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use
Cold water access, with our communal plunge pool or, if you fancy, a dip in the Royal Docks
Cold water access, with our communal plunge pool or, if you fancy, a dip in the Royal Docks
Salt and coffee scrubs for self-guided peelings
Salt and coffee scrubs for self-guided peelings
Food and drinks available to purchase on site
Food and drinks available to purchase on site
Space to socialise, stretch out, or just sit in the sun between rounds
Space to socialise, stretch out, or just sit in the sun between rounds
Come for a short session or stay all night and enjoy one of London’s most unique sauna experiences.
Your ticket includes access from 6-10pm. You’re welcome to come and go as you please. Swimwear is required until 8pm, after which guests are welcome to sauna without swimwear in line with continental sauna practice. Towels are always required inside the sauna. More details at sweheatsauna.co.uk .
Early bird tickets are £40 until 10/01/26 using code EARLYBIRD . After that, standard pricing is £60.
Special guest:
Duygan has been working as a show Aufguss master for many years, during which he has  gained extensive experience in both classical and creative show Aufguss formats. His  background includes successful participation in a Newcomer Challenge, numerous guest performances in various saunas, and continuous development in choreography, scent concepts and guest engagement.
Looking ahead, his upcoming experience includes participation in the German Show Aufguss Championships in April. In addition, he will be performing in May at one of the largest sauna events in Poland, held in the Colosseum, which will further expand his international experience.
Dougan's Aufguss style combines precise towel techniques, well-balanced fragrance concepts and music, as well as clear and respectful communication with guests, always happy to adapt his performance to the atmosphere, audience and philosophy of the sauna space.

raw.title: Full Moon Sauna and Sound Ceremony.
raw.description:
18:30 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us for a two and a half hours of Sauna, Sound and Intention setting.
What to expect -
The evening will consist of four rounds in the Sauna space,
Purification - through Smudging the body and a guided visualization to cleanse the mind and infused steam for the body.
Intention - You will be asked to release what no longer serves you, we will use vocalisation and singing bowls for this process. As well as burning anything written down on paper to be transformed in the fire. Intention in the steam to activate in the space now made.
Grounding - Drum journey and Rain stick to feel the power of Mother Earth whilst immersed in the elemental Sauna.
Protection - Meditation with protective crystals and visualisation to strengthen the energy bodies.
The Fire Pit will be on (Weather permitting) for us to gather and drink tea together whilst sharing the space under the energy and power of the approaching full moon in Gemini.
Victoria’s previous incarnations to the Sauna world were in the areas of intuitive healing. Having trained as an Energy Medicine Practitioner and Sound Therapist.
Victoria regularly held Sound Baths using Gongs and other percussion instruments. She worked intuitively with the frequencies of Crystals and the Subtle energy bodies to effect change in the Human bio-field. This interest and through her profound experiences, led her to the womb-like space of the Sauna environment, naturally aligning with its potential for introspection and transformation.

Amberluna Apothecary’s Ellen returns to indulge us. She’ll be weaving her sensory rituals through the romantic love story told by Oliver of Mythic Sauna. The 2.5 hour sauna and storytelling ritual invites you to connect deeply with your body, your self-love and to your open heart.
This won't be some soft-eyed fairytale. Our ancient tale will conjure full-hearted, unreasonable, hopeless, gorgeous romance in all its expansive complexity. We deeply welcome you to come on a date with your gorgeous self, your beloved friend or your smouldering date.
Sensory rituals will build feelings of connectedness and wellbeing with traditional heart-opening and calming herbal teas and encourage sensual body-mind connection with a honey and rose herbal salt scrub. You will enjoy heart-centred aromatherapy throughout, and a final nourishing rosy oil self-massage for the body. We will finish our session with delicious chocolate morsels to replenish our blood sugar and leave our hearts feeling full and our love abundant. Then it's out into the night-time, skin tingling, hearts heated, eyes aglow.
Use code MYTHIC for £5 off your tickets until 07/02/26.

Join us on Sunday 15th February, 8–10pm, as Transient Radio guides you through a Deep Listening journey in the warmth of the sauna. DJ Bobby Bucys will be hosting the session and selecting the soundtrack for this immersive evening.
Bobby Bucys, the head honcho of Transient Radio, has been DJing and collecting music for over 25 years, playing an eclectic mix across London, Barcelona, and his hometown of Ipswich. His ambient track 11.11 was featured on The Chillout Tent’s latest compilation last summer, and he regularly hosts sauna sessions in his handmade sauna in Suffolk.
The Deep Listening session will include four rounds in the sauna, each accompanied by music curated to transport you into a deeply relaxed state of mind, body, and soul.

raw.description:
Thursday 19 February 2026
20:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat for a two-hour textile-free Aufguss Experience.
Aufguss rituals – hallmarks of European sauna culture – feature a sauna master guiding you through 15-minute rounds of heat, aromas, music, and towel-waving techniques that circulate the air and create the perfect sauna atmosphere.
Across three distinct rituals, you’ll move from traditional heat infusions to banya-inspired techniques. Between rounds, cool off in the fresh air or take a dip in the cold plunge. Each ritual is designed to relax, invigorate, and entertain – a fun, social, and refreshing way to spend your evening.
This is a textile-free session, as is common in European spas. Sauna without swimwear allows for a better sweat and a more hygienic experience. Just bring a towel large enough to sit on completely.
Whether you’re winding down after a long week, warming up for a night out, or just looking for something different to do with friends, Aufguss Experience is the perfect pick. First-timers, regulars, groups, and solo sauna-goers are all welcome.
Spaces are limited, so book now!

class_type.description:
A two-hour guided experience exploring red light, sauna, and cold to reset the nervous system and deepen recovery.
Begin under BON CHARGE red light masks with breathwork and meditation, before moving into an ARC contrast journey led by ARC Co-founder Alanna - grounded in our signature rituals, somatic guidance, and state-shift sequencing.

We’ll close with an intimate expert panel on red light therapy, contrast, and modern recovery with BON CHARGE founders, ARC Co-founder Alanna, and Dr. Nima, Founder of Remedi London

class_type.name: Ground - Breathe & ground

class_type.description:
A guided journey through the lounge, sauna, and ice bath chambers, designed to support physical and neurological rewiring. 

This class works with body’s fascial system — the connective tissue network that responds to breath, temperature, nerves, and slow, spiralling movement.

Fascia is deeply connected to the brain and sensory nerves. By moving with awareness, we stimulate neural rewiring, enhancing communication through the body’s natural electrical pathways — fascia, water, and neuro-impulses. Contrast exposure sharpens awareness, boosts adaptability, and creates a clear reset for both body and mind.

Expect to feel more spacious in your body, calm, clear, and grounded in your natural, baseline nervous system. 

No experience needed. Move slowly, feel deeply, let go.

Event Schedule

🕠 4.15pm – 5.15pm · Barry’s East Class
Meet at Barry's East for a start strong with the iconic Red Room sweat session.

🕡 5.15pm – 5.45pm · Shake & Stroll
Refuel with a Barrys shake and walk round the corner with the crew.

🕖 5.45pm – 6.45pm · Contrast Therapy & Social
Reset with hot Finnish and infrared saunas and cold plunges at 3°, 6°, and 9°, then unwind with drinks, chats, and good vibes.

🕖 6.45pm - 7.00pm · Close

Sweat hard. Recover deeper. Connect stronger.

Limited spots available, an social evening of movement, recovery, and community.

🔥 Secure your spot. Sweat. Reset. Repeat!

A Galentine’s wellness social designed to slow down together. Gather with your girls for sauna and cold plunge rituals, intention setting, and feel-good moments of connection. Come as you are, laugh, unwind, and leave feeling deeply refreshed, supported, and celebrated- by yourself and by each other.

6:00 – 6:15 | Welcome
Arrive, exhale. Soft music, warm lighting, robes, towels, and a hydration station set the tone. You’ll receive an intention card and journal to guide your evening.

6:15 – 7:00 | Sauna & Plunge Ritual
A guided ritual, not a challenge. Gentle breath cues, soundbath music, and full permission to move, pause, or opt out as your body needs.

7:00 – 7:15 | Connection
Rest and reconnect in our Dry Off space with blankets, hydration, and light snacks.

7:15 – 7:45 | Studio
Settle into a 30-minute restorative and meditative studio session to calm your nervous system.

7:45 – 8:15 | Connection & Intention
Reflect in your journal, capture what surfaced, and set an intention to carry forward. We close with a grounding moment together.

Each guest leaves with a small grounding token (journal & tote) to take the experience with you.

events.event_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.session_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.sessionName: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai
raw.level:
Join us for a very special Galentines banya with Sasha Davai. 

Banya is a traditional Slavic bathing practice, similar to a sauna, but with slightly lower heat and higher humidity, designed to soften the body and deepen the effects of steam.

The session unfolds over two to three guided steam cycles and includes special herbal steam inhalations, honey and salt scrubs, oak-leaf whisking, and cooling ice massage. We'll also drink specially brewed tea. 

Each element is introduced gently, allowing time for rest, integration, and connection.

This session is ideal if you:

Are curious about banya or guided sauna rituals

Enjoy sensory, ritual-led experiences

Want something nurturing, grounding, and communal

Are looking for a slower, more intentional sauna experience

Join us for a unique evening combining the joy of singing with the relaxation of sauna. 

This special session brings together sauna ritual and singing meditation - two powerful practices for grounding the body, calming the nervous system, and creating connection.

We’ll begin with 40 minutes in the sauna, allowing heat, steam and stillness to help you soften, slow down, and arrive fully in your body. After cooling and settling, we’ll transition into 40 minutes of Singing Meditation, led live from the keyboard by Jacob, founder of Singing Meditation.

Jacob is a professional musician and daily meditator who discovered that singing can be one of the most accessible ways to deepen presence and focus - no prior meditation or musical experience required.

Using a simple call-and-response format, Jacob guides the group through gentle songs and mantras, building two- and three-part harmonies organically. There’s no sheet music, no pressure, and no “right” way to participate. You’re invited to:

Sing the main melody
Explore harmonies or improvisation
Or simply listen and absorb the sound

At the heart of this session is choice, accessibility, and shared calm. Whether you sing or stay quiet, sound becomes a meditative tool, something you can lean into, rather than perform.

This is a warm, inclusive space designed to help you drop out of your head, reconnect with your breath, and experience rest through rhythm and resonance.

No singing experience needed.
Just come as you are.

Join us at Sweheat for three rounds of ‘Saunagus’, a unique experience that combines heat, essential oils and music alongside your sauna experience.
By trained ‘gus master’ Oliver, he will deliver this traditional Danish ritual by using towel-swinging techniques to disperse the hot steam rhythmically to the music in every 15-minute long session.
Pure, organic essential oils compressed in ice balls placed on the sauna’s stove slowly disperses an aromatic steam which enhances the health properties of the experience.
Different essential oils can be utilised for different outcomes. For instance, peppermint can be used as a revitalising oil, lavender for calm and eucalyptus to clear the airways.
Each week the sessions will be themed through the scent of the essential oils, the music and movement to create a stimulating, relaxing or detoxifying effect on your body.
The ritual will leave you feeling both mentally and physically revived. Benefits range from a meditative state of mind to improving cardiovascular strength, boosting the immune system, as well as alleviating pain.

raw.description:
Thursday 25 September 2025
18:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat Sauna for a supper club and social as we enjoy the rare opportunity to enjoy Rekindling - fire art installation from the warmth and comfort of our Sauna spaces.
French fire alchemists, Compagnie Carabosse and Royal Docks communities combine to create Rekindling, an evocative fire installation on land and water. Rekindling explores the metamorphosis of the Royal Docks. Built during the Industrial Revolution as the largest enclosed docks in the world, Royal Docks aided London’s growth as a global city. Now the area is reemerging as a centre for enterprise, innovation and culture powered by its diverse communities, pioneering spirit, and global links.
One of France’s most important street arts groups, Compagnie Carabosse have delighted thousands of visitors across the world with their work. The installation will make best use of the reflective surfaces of London City Hall and the Dock side water scape, making the atmosphere of this area come alive with its elemental nature.
Sweheat will provide access to both Saunas, fire pit, BBQ area and hot Jacket Potatoes.
Bring your own fillings and alcoholic beverages to be enjoyed throughout the evening as we wander through the art installation together or alone. Coming back to Sweheat for a perfect sweat and social time.

raw.title: Sparkling Sauna - Lithuanian Sauna Ritual.
raw.description:
18:00 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
“Ivan Beats The Gong” together with “Sweheat Sauna” invites you to a special sauna evening in London.
The ritual will be guided by sauna master Silvija, who is a herbalist and founder of Birch House Rituals. She carries Lithuanian plant and sauna traditions, inviting people to reconnect with nature and themselves.
The ritual is going to take participants on a four-stage journey: starting with a gentle introduction to the heat, followed by salt therapy and whisking, then a refreshing shower of sparkling mineral water, and finally a calming mask to close the evening.
It’s an experience where heat, aromas, and natural elements come together to open up a whole new dimension of the sauna.
Only 20 spots available, hurry up to register!
Round 1 – Gentle introduction to heat
The evening begins softly: mild temperature, deep breathing, essential oils, and the cooling flow of fans help the body settle. A sip of mineral water refreshes from within as the body gets acquainted with the warmth.
Round 2 – Salt therapy
Salt particles spread through the sauna – breathing becomes clearer, the skin softer, and circulation more active. A magnesium salt massage on the skin revitalizes, while mineral water helps restore balance.
Round 3 – Whisking and a refreshing full-body experience
The heat intensifies. Whisks and compresses embrace the whole body, while slowly poured sparkling mineral water over the head creates a light tingling sensation and a refreshing release.
Round 4 – Farewell to the heat
A short and concentrated finale. A nourishing face mask made of honey, oil, and mineral water soothes the skin. The ritual closes with one last pour of mineral water and a calm return to presence.
Event dates: October 23 & 24, 18:00 – 21:00
Open to men and women.

Step into a deliciously dark fairytale this Halloween, where scented steam, candlelight, and ancient stories entwine. Join us for an immersive Mythic Sauna experience — a night of storytelling, ritual, and wonder as we honour the turning of the seasons.

Join us at Sweheat for a two-hour textile-free Aufguss Experience.
Aufguss rituals – hallmarks of European sauna culture – feature a sauna master guiding you through 15-minute rounds of heat, aromas, music, and towel-waving techniques that circulate the air and create the perfect sauna atmosphere.

raw.title: Traditional Lithuanian Pirtis Ritual with Birch House Rituals.
raw.description:
Saturday 6 December 2025
18:00 20:00
Google Calendar ICS
Step into a slow, sensory evening rooted in the ancestral sauna traditions of the Baltic lands - led by Silvija, founder of Birch House Rituals.
This ritual draws on her Lithuanian heritage, weaving together the wisdom of the Pirtis with herbal medicine, folklore and plant spirit. Guided by the rhythms of the season and the healing power of trees and wild plants, you’ll be invited to soften, release, and return to presence.
Held in the warmth of the sauna, aromatic steam mingles with wild-foraged salt scrubs, raw honey, and hand-crafted whisks to create a space of deep restoration and reconnection.
Rooted in tree energetics, infused with plant essences, and dusted with whispers of Baltic amber, this is a body prayer - a communion with the wisdom of the Earth.
Expect:
Guided Lithuanian Pirtis ritual
Handmade herbal salt scrubs + raw honey facials
Halotherapy + aromatic steam
Plant-whisking and seasonal energetics
Subtle ritual elements rooted in Baltic nature

raw.title: Let’s Glow - NYE Party
raw.description:
Wednesday 31 December 2025 20:00 Thursday 1 January 2026 01:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us as we say goodbye to 2025 with our second Neon, New Years Eve celebration at Sweheat sauna.
Wear your best NEON glow sauna wear and we will provide the body paints and glow sticks.
Joining us this year will be two of the UKs best Sauna Masters, Oliver from Saunagus UK and Wendy Liu from Saunawave.
Both of our Saunas will be lit up with rituals and lights to create a perfect atmosphere to release the departing year and welcoming in the new. From leaf whisking to aromatherapy to ice infusions we will provide the right heat for a great evening.
You will be greeted at Sweheat Sauna with a hot Cacao drink to get the evening off to a fabulous start.
There will be music playing from our DJ Booth to get the party started, whilst we adorn the body with paints and good wishes for the new year. We will have an added extra space with a large Sauna Tent as our chill out zone for a less intense and social experience.
After some themed and theatrical Saunatainment from our fabulous Sauna Masters we will venture to the Dock side to watch the fireworks from the surrounding area.
We will wind down the evening with some more heat and time to socialise before dipping in the dock, bare if you dare just before we wrap up the evening.
There will be snacks and an area for BBQing so bring your bangers and something to share.
Cold drinks will be on sale but feel free to bring a bottle if you fancy something stronger for your celebrations.
More details to follow so be sure to sign up to our socials via Facebook or Instagram.

Join us for a full evening of special aufguss rituals from top sauna masters, access to multiple saunas, and plenty of time and space to hang out and unwind.
Lange Saunanacht (German for “long sauna night”) is a full-evening sauna experience, our take on a common German sauna tradition.
We're bringing you:
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use

Salt and coffee scrubs for self-guided peelings
Food and drinks available to purchase on site

Space to socialise, stretch out, or just sit in the sun between rounds
Come for a short session or stay all night and enjoy one of London’s most unique sauna experiences.
Your ticket includes access from 6-10pm. You’re welcome to come and go as you please. Swimwear is required until 8pm, after which guests are welcome to sauna without swimwear in line with continental sauna practice. Towels are always required inside the sauna. More details at sweheatsauna.co.uk .
Early bird tickets are £40 until 10/01/26 using code EARLYBIRD . After that, standard pricing is £60.
Special guest:
Duygan has been working as a show Aufguss master for many years, during which he has  gained extensive experience in both classical and creative show Aufguss formats. His  background includes successful participation in a Newcomer Challenge, numerous guest performances in various saunas, and continuous development in choreography, scent concepts and guest engagement.
Looking ahead, his upcoming experience includes participation in the German Show Aufguss Championships in April. In addition, he will be performing in May at one of the largest sauna events in Poland, held in the Colosseum, which will further expand his international experience.
Dougan's Aufguss style combines precise towel techniques, well-balanced fragrance concepts and music, as well as clear and respectful communication with guests, always happy to adapt his performance to the atmosphere, audience and philosophy of the sauna space.

raw.title: Full Moon Sauna and Sound Ceremony.
raw.description:
18:30 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us for a two and a half hours of Sauna, Sound and Intention setting.
What to expect -
The evening will consist of four rounds in the Sauna space,
Purification - through Smudging the body and a guided visualization to cleanse the mind and infused steam for the body.
Intention - You will be asked to release what no longer serves you, we will use vocalisation and singing bowls for this process. As well as burning anything written down on paper to be transformed in the fire. Intention in the steam to activate in the space now made.
Grounding - Drum journey and Rain stick to feel the power of Mother Earth whilst immersed in the elemental Sauna.
Protection - Meditation with protective crystals and visualisation to strengthen the energy bodies.
The Fire Pit will be on (Weather permitting) for us to gather and drink tea together whilst sharing the space under the energy and power of the approaching full moon in Gemini.
Victoria’s previous incarnations to the Sauna world were in the areas of intuitive healing. Having trained as an Energy Medicine Practitioner and Sound Therapist.
Victoria regularly held Sound Baths using Gongs and other percussion instruments. She worked intuitively with the frequencies of Crystals and the Subtle energy bodies to effect change in the Human bio-field. This interest and through her profound experiences, led her to the womb-like space of the Sauna environment, naturally aligning with its potential for introspection and transformation.

Join Mythic Sauna this Valentine's and experience a multisensory love story in the wood-fired sauna.
Amberluna Apothecary’s Ellen returns to indulge us. She’ll be weaving her sensory rituals through the romantic love story told by Oliver of Mythic Sauna. The 2.5 hour sauna and storytelling ritual invites you to connect deeply with your body, your self-love and to your open heart.
This won't be some soft-eyed fairytale. Our ancient tale will conjure full-hearted, unreasonable, hopeless, gorgeous romance in all its expansive complexity. We deeply welcome you to come on a date with your gorgeous self, your beloved friend or your smouldering date.
Sensory rituals will build feelings of connectedness and wellbeing with traditional heart-opening and calming herbal teas and encourage sensual body-mind connection with a honey and rose herbal salt scrub. You will enjoy heart-centred aromatherapy throughout, and a final nourishing rosy oil self-massage for the body. We will finish our session with delicious chocolate morsels to replenish our blood sugar and leave our hearts feeling full and our love abundant. Then it's out into the night-time, skin tingling, hearts heated, eyes aglow.

Aufguss rituals – hallmarks of European sauna culture – feature a sauna master guiding you through 15-minute rounds of heat, aromas, music, and towel-waving techniques that circulate the air and create the perfect sauna atmosphere.
Across three distinct rituals, you’ll move from traditional heat infusions to banya-inspired techniques. Between rounds, cool off in the fresh air or take a dip in the cold plunge. Each ritual is designed to relax, invigorate, and entertain – a fun, social, and refreshing way to spend your evening.
This is a textile-free session, as is common in European spas. Sauna without swimwear allows for a better sweat and a more hygienic experience. Just bring a towel large enough to sit on completely.
Whether you’re winding down after a long week, warming up for a night out, or just looking for something different to do with friends, Aufguss Experience is the perfect pick. First-timers, regulars, groups, and solo sauna-goers are all welcome.
Spaces are limited, so book now!

class_type.description:
A two-hour guided experience exploring red light, sauna, and cold to reset the nervous system and deepen recovery.
Begin under BON CHARGE red light masks with breathwork and meditation, before moving into an ARC contrast journey led by ARC Co-founder Alanna - grounded in our signature rituals, somatic guidance, and state-shift sequencing.

We’ll close with an intimate expert panel on red light therapy, contrast, and modern recovery with BON CHARGE founders, ARC Co-founder Alanna, and Dr. Nima, Founder of Remedi London

class_type.description:
A guided journey through the lounge, sauna, and ice bath chambers, designed to support physical and neurological rewiring. 

This class works with body’s fascial system — the connective tissue network that responds to breath, temperature, nerves, and slow, spiralling movement.

Fascia is deeply connected to the brain and sensory nerves. By moving with awareness, we stimulate neural rewiring, enhancing communication through the body’s natural electrical pathways — fascia, water, and neuro-impulses. Contrast exposure sharpens awareness, boosts adaptability, and creates a clear reset for both body and mind.

Expect to feel more spacious in your body, calm, clear, and grounded in your natural, baseline nervous system. 

No experience needed. Move slowly, feel deeply, let go.

Expect a deep reset: muscles loosen, breath expands, and the body finds its rhythm again.

class_type.description: A fully guided class in arc’s sauna and cold plunge chamber, this session leads you through long-hold Yin postures to release tension in the neck, shoulders, and arms — areas that often hold both physical and emotional weight. Join us for a celebratory edition of our signature Sound Bath class, crafted to lift your mood, boost your energy, and deepen your sense of connection. This fully guided experience weaves together sauna, ice baths, and lounge time with carefully curated modalities that support your brain’s natural feel-good chemistry.

This guided session invites you to step out of the mind and into your body. Through functional breathwork and yin-inspired movement, we release tension in the shoulders — a common place for stored stress and emotional weight. Sauna and cold plunges support nervous system regulation, building resilience and helping the mind settle into presence. The practice closes with sound therapy using crystal singing bowls, designed to shift brainwaves, promote relaxation, and leave you feeling clear, centered, and deeply connected.

After class, enjoy your complimentary AKT Deodorant — the perfect finishing touch to feel refreshed inside and out.

class_type.description: A fully guided class in arc’s sauna and cold plunge chamber, this session leads you through long-hold Yin postures to release tension in the neck, shoulders, and arms — areas that often hold both physical and emotional weight. You’ll then shift into the invigorating contrast of a group cold plunge to awaken circulation and sharpen presence, before moving into Yoga Nidra (sleep yoga) — a deeply restorative guided rest. The practice closes with a final cold immersion and circle of sharing, leaving you grounded, open, and renewed.

events.event_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.session_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.sessionName: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai
raw.level:
Join us for a very special Galentines banya with Sasha Davai. 

Banya is a traditional Slavic bathing practice, similar to a sauna, but with slightly lower heat and higher humidity, designed to soften the body and deepen the effects of steam.

The session unfolds over two to three guided steam cycles and includes special herbal steam inhalations, honey and salt scrubs, oak-leaf whisking, and cooling ice massage. We'll also drink specially brewed tea. 

Each element is introduced gently, allowing time for rest, integration, and connection.

This session is ideal if you:

Are curious about banya or guided sauna rituals

Enjoy sensory, ritual-led experiences

Want something nurturing, grounding, and communal

Are looking for a slower, more intentional sauna experience

Join us for a unique evening combining the joy of singing with the relaxation of sauna. 

This special session brings together sauna ritual and singing meditation - two powerful practices for grounding the body, calming the nervous system, and creating connection.

We’ll begin with 40 minutes in the sauna, allowing heat, steam and stillness to help you soften, slow down, and arrive fully in your body. After cooling and settling, we’ll transition into 40 minutes of Singing Meditation, led live from the keyboard by Jacob, founder of Singing Meditation.

Jacob is a professional musician and daily meditator who discovered that singing can be one of the most accessible ways to deepen presence and focus - no prior meditation or musical experience required.

Using a simple call-and-response format, Jacob guides the group through gentle songs and mantras, building two- and three-part harmonies organically. There’s no sheet music, no pressure, and no “right” way to participate. You’re invited to:

Sing the main melody
Explore harmonies or improvisation
Or simply listen and absorb the sound

At the heart of this session is choice, accessibility, and shared calm. Whether you sing or stay quiet, sound becomes a meditative tool, something you can lean into, rather than perform.

This is a warm, inclusive space designed to help you drop out of your head, reconnect with your breath, and experience rest through rhythm and resonance.

No singing experience needed.
Just come as you are.

raw.title: Saunagus Session.
raw.description:
Saturday 28 June 2025
20:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat for three rounds of ‘Saunagus’, a unique experience that combines heat, essential oils and music alongside your sauna experience.
By trained ‘gus master’ Oliver, he will deliver this traditional Danish ritual by using towel-swinging techniques to disperse the hot steam rhythmically to the music in every 15-minute long session.
Pure, organic essential oils compressed in ice balls placed on the sauna’s stove slowly disperses an aromatic steam which enhances the health properties of the experience.
Different essential oils can be utilised for different outcomes. For instance, peppermint can be used as a revitalising oil, lavender for calm and eucalyptus to clear the airways.
Each week the sessions will be themed through the scent of the essential oils, the music and movement to create a stimulating, relaxing or detoxifying effect on your body.
The ritual will leave you feeling both mentally and physically revived. Benefits range from a meditative state of mind to improving cardiovascular strength, boosting the immune system, as well as alleviating pain.

Join us at Sweheat for three rounds of ‘Saunagus’, a unique experience that combines heat, essential oils and music alongside your sauna experience.
By trained ‘gus master’ Oliver, he will deliver this traditional Danish ritual by using towel-swinging techniques to disperse the hot steam rhythmically to the music in every 15-minute long session.
Pure, organic essential oils compressed in ice balls placed on the sauna’s stove slowly disperses an aromatic steam which enhances the health properties of the experience.
Different essential oils can be utilised for different outcomes. For instance, peppermint can be used as a revitalising oil, lavender for calm and eucalyptus to clear the airways.
Each week the sessions will be themed through the scent of the essential oils, the music and movement to create a stimulating, relaxing or detoxifying effect on your body.
The ritual will leave you feeling both mentally and physically revived. Benefits range from a meditative state of mind to improving cardiovascular strength, boosting the immune system, as well as alleviating pain.

raw.title: Rekindling - Sauna Social and Supper Club.
raw.description:
Thursday 25 September 2025
18:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat Sauna for a supper club and social as we enjoy the rare opportunity to enjoy Rekindling - fire art installation from the warmth and comfort of our Sauna spaces.
French fire alchemists, Compagnie Carabosse and Royal Docks communities combine to create Rekindling, an evocative fire installation on land and water. Rekindling explores the metamorphosis of the Royal Docks. Built during the Industrial Revolution as the largest enclosed docks in the world, Royal Docks aided London’s growth as a global city. Now the area is reemerging as a centre for enterprise, innovation and culture powered by its diverse communities, pioneering spirit, and global links.
One of France’s most important street arts groups, Compagnie Carabosse have delighted thousands of visitors across the world with their work. The installation will make best use of the reflective surfaces of London City Hall and the Dock side water scape, making the atmosphere of this area come alive with its elemental nature.
Sweheat will provide access to both Saunas, fire pit, BBQ area and hot Jacket Potatoes.
Bring your own fillings and alcoholic beverages to be enjoyed throughout the evening as we wander through the art installation together or alone. Coming back to Sweheat for a perfect sweat and social time.

raw.title: Sparkling Sauna - Lithuanian Sauna Ritual.
raw.description:
18:00 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
“Ivan Beats The Gong” together with “Sweheat Sauna” invites you to a special sauna evening in London.
The ritual will be guided by sauna master Silvija, who is a herbalist and founder of Birch House Rituals. She carries Lithuanian plant and sauna traditions, inviting people to reconnect with nature and themselves.
The ritual is going to take participants on a four-stage journey: starting with a gentle introduction to the heat, followed by salt therapy and whisking, then a refreshing shower of sparkling mineral water, and finally a calming mask to close the evening.
It’s an experience where heat, aromas, and natural elements come together to open up a whole new dimension of the sauna.
Only 20 spots available, hurry up to register!
Round 1 – Gentle introduction to heat
The evening begins softly: mild temperature, deep breathing, essential oils, and the cooling flow of fans help the body settle. A sip of mineral water refreshes from within as the body gets acquainted with the warmth.
Round 2 – Salt therapy
Salt particles spread through the sauna – breathing becomes clearer, the skin softer, and circulation more active. A magnesium salt massage on the skin revitalizes, while mineral water helps restore balance.
Round 3 – Whisking and a refreshing full-body experience
The heat intensifies. Whisks and compresses embrace the whole body, while slowly poured sparkling mineral water over the head creates a light tingling sensation and a refreshing release.
Round 4 – Farewell to the heat
A short and concentrated finale. A nourishing face mask made of honey, oil, and mineral water soothes the skin. The ritual closes with one last pour of mineral water and a calm return to presence.
Event dates: October 23 & 24, 18:00 – 21:00
Open to men and women.

19:00 21:30

Step into a deliciously dark fairytale this Halloween, where scented steam, candlelight, and ancient stories entwine. Join us for an immersive Mythic Sauna experience — a night of storytelling, ritual, and wonder as we honour the turning of the seasons.
Woven through four sauna sessions, expert storyteller Oliver Wallace will tell a chilling fairytale from the deep mythic roots of northern Europe. Between sessions we will cold plunge, sip wild-foraged tea, and share pumpkin soup around the fire as we prepare for the longer nights ahead.
As the nights draw in and the veil between worlds thins, we gather in community to meet the dark — and remember that warmth, laughter, and story can carry us safely through it.

raw.title: Let’s Glow - NYE Party
raw.description:
Wednesday 31 December 2025 20:00 Thursday 1 January 2026 01:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us as we say goodbye to 2025 with our second Neon, New Years Eve celebration at Sweheat sauna.
Wear your best NEON glow sauna wear and we will provide the body paints and glow sticks.
Joining us this year will be two of the UKs best Sauna Masters, Oliver from Saunagus UK and Wendy Liu from Saunawave.
Both of our Saunas will be lit up with rituals and lights to create a perfect atmosphere to release the departing year and welcoming in the new. From leaf whisking to aromatherapy to ice infusions we will provide the right heat for a great evening.
You will be greeted at Sweheat Sauna with a hot Cacao drink to get the evening off to a fabulous start.
There will be music playing from our DJ Booth to get the party started, whilst we adorn the body with paints and good wishes for the new year. We will have an added extra space with a large Sauna Tent as our chill out zone for a less intense and social experience.
After some themed and theatrical Saunatainment from our fabulous Sauna Masters we will venture to the Dock side to watch the fireworks from the surrounding area.
We will wind down the evening with some more heat and time to socialise before dipping in the dock, bare if you dare just before we wrap up the evening.
There will be snacks and an area for BBQing so bring your bangers and something to share.
Cold drinks will be on sale but feel free to bring a bottle if you fancy something stronger for your celebrations.
More details to follow so be sure to sign up to our socials via Facebook or Instagram.

Join us for a full evening of special aufguss rituals from top sauna masters, access to multiple saunas, and plenty of time and space to hang out and unwind.
Lange Saunanacht (German for “long sauna night”) is a full-evening sauna experience, our take on a common German sauna tradition.
We're bringing you:
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use
Cold water access, with our communal plunge pool or, if you fancy, a dip in the Royal Docks
Cold water access, with our communal plunge pool or, if you fancy, a dip in the Royal Docks
Salt and coffee scrubs for self-guided peelings
Salt and coffee scrubs for self-guided peelings
Food and drinks available to purchase on site
Food and drinks available to purchase on site
Space to socialise, stretch out, or just sit in the sun between rounds
Space to socialise, stretch out, or just sit in the sun between rounds
Come for a short session or stay all night and enjoy one of London’s most unique sauna experiences.
Your ticket includes access from 6-10pm. You’re welcome to come and go as you please. Swimwear is required until 8pm, after which guests are welcome to sauna without swimwear in line with continental sauna practice. Towels are always required inside the sauna. More details at sweheatsauna.co.uk .
Early bird tickets are £40 until 10/01/26 using code EARLYBIRD . After that, standard pricing is £60.
Special guest:
Duygan has been working as a show Aufguss master for many years, during which he has  gained extensive experience in both classical and creative show Aufguss formats. His  background includes successful participation in a Newcomer Challenge, numerous guest performances in various saunas, and continuous development in choreography, scent concepts and guest engagement.
Looking ahead, his upcoming experience includes participation in the German Show Aufguss Championships in April. In addition, he will be performing in May at one of the largest sauna events in Poland, held in the Colosseum, which will further expand his international experience.
Dougan's Aufguss style combines precise towel techniques, well-balanced fragrance concepts and music, as well as clear and respectful communication with guests, always happy to adapt his performance to the atmosphere, audience and philosophy of the sauna space.

raw.title: Full Moon Sauna and Sound Ceremony.
raw.description:
18:30 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us for a two and a half hours of Sauna, Sound and Intention setting.
What to expect -
The evening will consist of four rounds in the Sauna space,
Purification - through Smudging the body and a guided visualization to cleanse the mind and infused steam for the body.
Intention - You will be asked to release what no longer serves you, we will use vocalisation and singing bowls for this process. As well as burning anything written down on paper to be transformed in the fire. Intention in the steam to activate in the space now made.
Grounding - Drum journey and Rain stick to feel the power of Mother Earth whilst immersed in the elemental Sauna.
Protection - Meditation with protective crystals and visualisation to strengthen the energy bodies.
The Fire Pit will be on (Weather permitting) for us to gather and drink tea together whilst sharing the space under the energy and power of the approaching full moon in Gemini.
Victoria’s previous incarnations to the Sauna world were in the areas of intuitive healing. Having trained as an Energy Medicine Practitioner and Sound Therapist.
Victoria regularly held Sound Baths using Gongs and other percussion instruments. She worked intuitively with the frequencies of Crystals and the Subtle energy bodies to effect change in the Human bio-field. This interest and through her profound experiences, led her to the womb-like space of the Sauna environment, naturally aligning with its potential for introspection and transformation.

raw.description:
Saturday 14 February 2026
19:00 21:30
Google Calendar ICS
Join Mythic Sauna this Valentine's and experience a multisensory love story in the wood-fired sauna.
Amberluna Apothecary’s Ellen returns to indulge us. She’ll be weaving her sensory rituals through the romantic love story told by Oliver of Mythic Sauna. The 2.5 hour sauna and storytelling ritual invites you to connect deeply with your body, your self-love and to your open heart.
This won't be some soft-eyed fairytale. Our ancient tale will conjure full-hearted, unreasonable, hopeless, gorgeous romance in all its expansive complexity. We deeply welcome you to come on a date with your gorgeous self, your beloved friend or your smouldering date.
Sensory rituals will build feelings of connectedness and wellbeing with traditional heart-opening and calming herbal teas and encourage sensual body-mind connection with a honey and rose herbal salt scrub. You will enjoy heart-centred aromatherapy throughout, and a final nourishing rosy oil self-massage for the body. We will finish our session with delicious chocolate morsels to replenish our blood sugar and leave our hearts feeling full and our love abundant. Then it's out into the night-time, skin tingling, hearts heated, eyes aglow.
Use code MYTHIC for £5 off your tickets until 07/02/26.

Connect with breath work, movement, and release pent up energy. Through these integrative practices you’ll ground into the body, find inner stability, and clarity.
class_type.name: Ground - Breathe & ground

class_type.description:
A guided journey through the lounge, sauna, and ice bath chambers, designed to support physical and neurological rewiring. 

This class works with body’s fascial system — the connective tissue network that responds to breath, temperature, nerves, and slow, spiralling movement.

Fascia is deeply connected to the brain and sensory nerves. By moving with awareness, we stimulate neural rewiring, enhancing communication through the body’s natural electrical pathways — fascia, water, and neuro-impulses. Contrast exposure sharpens awareness, boosts adaptability, and creates a clear reset for both body and mind.

Expect to feel more spacious in your body, calm, clear, and grounded in your natural, baseline nervous system. 

No experience needed. Move slowly, feel deeply, let go.
class_type.name: Relax - Letting Go

class_type.description:
A fully guided class in the sauna and ice baths to reset your brain’s reward and satisfaction pathways. 

Through ice baths, breath work, meditation, and mental rewiring, we boost healthy dopamine release, break old habits, and shift your focus to intrinsic motivation. Unlock new levels of growth and peak experiences.
class_type.name: Ground - Dopamine Reset

Expect a deep reset: muscles loosen, breath expands, and the body finds its rhythm again.

Expect a hands-on, educational, and deeply restorative session—because your own hands are your most powerful healing tool.

class_type.description:
Kick off your morning with our ARC x Lululemon Run Club, featuring run ambassadors and pacers to keep you motivated every step of the way. Celebrate your effort with Arc Recovery, where a guided post-run session supports your body from warm-up to full reset.

Schedule:
8:30 – 9:00 | Guests drop bags & check in
9:00 – 9:45 | 5km Run with Chris Baxter
9:45 – 10:00 | Cool down into Arc
10:00 – 11:00 | Guided Stretch & Recover class with Eva Syti

This fully guided recovery class combines breathwork, fascial release, strength work, and lymphatic drainage to accelerate recovery, enhance mobility, reduce tension, and support optimal performance — perfect after a run or a demanding week.

After class, grab a complimentary Lululemon water bottle — the perfect finish to fuel your body and keep you moving at your best.
class_type.name: Stretch & Recover x Lululemon Run Club

The practice closes with a final cold immersion and circle of sharing, leaving you grounded, open, and renewed.

Event Schedule

🕠 4.15pm – 5.15pm · Barry’s East Class
Meet at Barry's East for a start strong with the iconic Red Room sweat session.

🕡 5.15pm – 5.45pm · Shake & Stroll
Refuel with a Barrys shake and walk round the corner with the crew.

🕖 5.45pm – 6.45pm · Contrast Therapy & Social
Reset with hot Finnish and infrared saunas and cold plunges at 3°, 6°, and 9°, then unwind with drinks, chats, and good vibes.

🕖 6.45pm - 7.00pm · Close

Sweat hard. Recover deeper. Connect stronger.

Limited spots available, an social evening of movement, recovery, and community.

🔥 Secure your spot. Sweat. Reset. Repeat!

A Galentine’s wellness social designed to slow down together. Gather with your girls for sauna and cold plunge rituals, intention setting, and feel-good moments of connection. Come as you are, laugh, unwind, and leave feeling deeply refreshed, supported, and celebrated- by yourself and by each other.

6:00 – 6:15 | Welcome
Arrive, exhale. Soft music, warm lighting, robes, towels, and a hydration station set the tone. You’ll receive an intention card and journal to guide your evening.

6:15 – 7:00 | Sauna & Plunge Ritual
A guided ritual, not a challenge. Gentle breath cues, soundbath music, and full permission to move, pause, or opt out as your body needs.

7:00 – 7:15 | Connection
Rest and reconnect in our Dry Off space with blankets, hydration, and light snacks.

7:15 – 7:45 | Studio
Settle into a 30-minute restorative and meditative studio session to calm your nervous system.

7:45 – 8:15 | Connection & Intention
Reflect in your journal, capture what surfaced, and set an intention to carry forward. We close with a grounding moment together.

Each guest leaves with a small grounding token (journal & tote) to take the experience with you.

EARLY BIRD: 0-4 Tickets - £30 
STANDARD: 5-8 Tickets - £40
FINAL TICKETS: 9-12 Tickets - £50

events.event_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.session_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.sessionName: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai
raw.level:
Join us for a very special Galentines banya with Sasha Davai. 

Banya is a traditional Slavic bathing practice, similar to a sauna, but with slightly lower heat and higher humidity, designed to soften the body and deepen the effects of steam.

The session unfolds over two to three guided steam cycles and includes special herbal steam inhalations, honey and salt scrubs, oak-leaf whisking, and cooling ice massage. We'll also drink specially brewed tea. 

Each element is introduced gently, allowing time for rest, integration, and connection.

This session is ideal if you:

Are curious about banya or guided sauna rituals

Enjoy sensory, ritual-led experiences

Want something nurturing, grounding, and communal

Are looking for a slower, more intentional sauna experience

Join us for a unique evening combining the joy of singing with the relaxation of sauna. 

This special session brings together sauna ritual and singing meditation - two powerful practices for grounding the body, calming the nervous system, and creating connection.

We’ll begin with 40 minutes in the sauna, allowing heat, steam and stillness to help you soften, slow down, and arrive fully in your body. After cooling and settling, we’ll transition into 40 minutes of Singing Meditation, led live from the keyboard by Jacob, founder of Singing Meditation.

Jacob is a professional musician and daily meditator who discovered that singing can be one of the most accessible ways to deepen presence and focus - no prior meditation or musical experience required.

Using a simple call-and-response format, Jacob guides the group through gentle songs and mantras, building two- and three-part harmonies organically. There’s no sheet music, no pressure, and no “right” way to participate. You’re invited to:

Sing the main melody
Explore harmonies or improvisation
Or simply listen and absorb the sound

At the heart of this session is choice, accessibility, and shared calm. Whether you sing or stay quiet, sound becomes a meditative tool, something you can lean into, rather than perform.

This is a warm, inclusive space designed to help you drop out of your head, reconnect with your breath, and experience rest through rhythm and resonance.

No singing experience needed.
Just come as you are.

raw.title: Saunagus Session.
raw.description:
Saturday 28 June 2025
20:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat for three rounds of ‘Saunagus’, a unique experience that combines heat, essential oils and music alongside your sauna experience.
By trained ‘gus master’ Oliver, he will deliver this traditional Danish ritual by using towel-swinging techniques to disperse the hot steam rhythmically to the music in every 15-minute long session.
Pure, organic essential oils compressed in ice balls placed on the sauna’s stove slowly disperses an aromatic steam which enhances the health properties of the experience.
Different essential oils can be utilised for different outcomes. For instance, peppermint can be used as a revitalising oil, lavender for calm and eucalyptus to clear the airways.
Each week the sessions will be themed through the scent of the essential oils, the music and movement to create a stimulating, relaxing or detoxifying effect on your body.
The ritual will leave you feeling both mentally and physically revived. Benefits range from a meditative state of mind to improving cardiovascular strength, boosting the immune system, as well as alleviating pain.

raw.title: Rekindling - Sauna Social and Supper Club.
raw.description:
Thursday 25 September 2025
18:00 22:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us at Sweheat Sauna for a supper club and social as we enjoy the rare opportunity to enjoy Rekindling - fire art installation from the warmth and comfort of our Sauna spaces.
French fire alchemists, Compagnie Carabosse and Royal Docks communities combine to create Rekindling, an evocative fire installation on land and water. Rekindling explores the metamorphosis of the Royal Docks. Built during the Industrial Revolution as the largest enclosed docks in the world, Royal Docks aided London’s growth as a global city. Now the area is reemerging as a centre for enterprise, innovation and culture powered by its diverse communities, pioneering spirit, and global links.
One of France’s most important street arts groups, Compagnie Carabosse have delighted thousands of visitors across the world with their work. The installation will make best use of the reflective surfaces of London City Hall and the Dock side water scape, making the atmosphere of this area come alive with its elemental nature.
Sweheat will provide access to both Saunas, fire pit, BBQ area and hot Jacket Potatoes.
Bring your own fillings and alcoholic beverages to be enjoyed throughout the evening as we wander through the art installation together or alone. Coming back to Sweheat for a perfect sweat and social time.

raw.title: Sparkling Sauna - Lithuanian Sauna Ritual.
raw.description:
18:00 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
“Ivan Beats The Gong” together with “Sweheat Sauna” invites you to a special sauna evening in London.
The ritual will be guided by sauna master Silvija, who is a herbalist and founder of Birch House Rituals. She carries Lithuanian plant and sauna traditions, inviting people to reconnect with nature and themselves.
The ritual is going to take participants on a four-stage journey: starting with a gentle introduction to the heat, followed by salt therapy and whisking, then a refreshing shower of sparkling mineral water, and finally a calming mask to close the evening.
It’s an experience where heat, aromas, and natural elements come together to open up a whole new dimension of the sauna.
Only 20 spots available, hurry up to register!
Round 1 – Gentle introduction to heat
The evening begins softly: mild temperature, deep breathing, essential oils, and the cooling flow of fans help the body settle. A sip of mineral water refreshes from within as the body gets acquainted with the warmth.
Round 2 – Salt therapy
Salt particles spread through the sauna – breathing becomes clearer, the skin softer, and circulation more active. A magnesium salt massage on the skin revitalizes, while mineral water helps restore balance.
Round 3 – Whisking and a refreshing full-body experience
The heat intensifies. Whisks and compresses embrace the whole body, while slowly poured sparkling mineral water over the head creates a light tingling sensation and a refreshing release.
Round 4 – Farewell to the heat
A short and concentrated finale. A nourishing face mask made of honey, oil, and mineral water soothes the skin. The ritual closes with one last pour of mineral water and a calm return to presence.
Event dates: October 23 & 24, 18:00 – 21:00
Open to men and women.

19:00 21:30

Step into a deliciously dark fairytale this Halloween, where scented steam, candlelight, and ancient stories entwine. Join us for an immersive Mythic Sauna experience — a night of storytelling, ritual, and wonder as we honour the turning of the seasons.
Woven through four sauna sessions, expert storyteller Oliver Wallace will tell a chilling fairytale from the deep mythic roots of northern Europe. Between sessions we will cold plunge, sip wild-foraged tea, and share pumpkin soup around the fire as we prepare for the longer nights ahead.
As the nights draw in and the veil between worlds thins, we gather in community to meet the dark — and remember that warmth, laughter, and story can carry us safely through it.
“It completely exceeded my expectations. Oliver’s storytelling captivated and inspired me.”
“It’s like coming out of the world out there, into this little oasis of peace and connection” “It was amazing to have so much presence with all the body sensations - with the heat, the scents, the cold, and the images that were forming.”
Find out about Oliver: www.linktr.ee/oliverwallacestories .

raw.title: Let’s Glow - NYE Party
raw.description:
Wednesday 31 December 2025 20:00 Thursday 1 January 2026 01:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us as we say goodbye to 2025 with our second Neon, New Years Eve celebration at Sweheat sauna.
Wear your best NEON glow sauna wear and we will provide the body paints and glow sticks.
Joining us this year will be two of the UKs best Sauna Masters, Oliver from Saunagus UK and Wendy Liu from Saunawave.
Both of our Saunas will be lit up with rituals and lights to create a perfect atmosphere to release the departing year and welcoming in the new. From leaf whisking to aromatherapy to ice infusions we will provide the right heat for a great evening.
You will be greeted at Sweheat Sauna with a hot Cacao drink to get the evening off to a fabulous start.
There will be music playing from our DJ Booth to get the party started, whilst we adorn the body with paints and good wishes for the new year. We will have an added extra space with a large Sauna Tent as our chill out zone for a less intense and social experience.
After some themed and theatrical Saunatainment from our fabulous Sauna Masters we will venture to the Dock side to watch the fireworks from the surrounding area.
We will wind down the evening with some more heat and time to socialise before dipping in the dock, bare if you dare just before we wrap up the evening.
There will be snacks and an area for BBQing so bring your bangers and something to share.

Join us for a full evening of special aufguss rituals from top sauna masters, access to multiple saunas, and plenty of time and space to hang out and unwind.
Lange Saunanacht (German for “long sauna night”) is a full-evening sauna experience, our take on a common German sauna tradition.
We're bringing you:
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Special guided Aufguss rituals led by some of the top sauna masters in the UK and Europe
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use
Access to two wood-fired saunas, one for guided aufguss rituals and the other for open use

Salt and coffee scrubs for self-guided peelings
Food and drinks available to purchase on site

Space to socialise, stretch out, or just sit in the sun between rounds
Come for a short session or stay all night and enjoy one of London’s most unique sauna experiences.
Your ticket includes access from 6-10pm. You’re welcome to come and go as you please. Swimwear is required until 8pm, after which guests are welcome to sauna without swimwear in line with continental sauna practice. Towels are always required inside the sauna. More details at sweheatsauna.co.uk .
Early bird tickets are £40 until 10/01/26 using code EARLYBIRD . After that, standard pricing is £60.
Special guest:
Duygan has been working as a show Aufguss master for many years, during which he has  gained extensive experience in both classical and creative show Aufguss formats. His  background includes successful participation in a Newcomer Challenge, numerous guest performances in various saunas, and continuous development in choreography, scent concepts and guest engagement.
Looking ahead, his upcoming experience includes participation in the German Show Aufguss Championships in April. In addition, he will be performing in May at one of the largest sauna events in Poland, held in the Colosseum, which will further expand his international experience.
Dougan's Aufguss style combines precise towel techniques, well-balanced fragrance concepts and music, as well as clear and respectful communication with guests, always happy to adapt his performance to the atmosphere, audience and philosophy of the sauna space.

raw.description:
18:30 21:00
Google Calendar ICS
Join us for a two and a half hours of Sauna, Sound and Intention setting.
What to expect -
The evening will consist of four rounds in the Sauna space,
Purification - through Smudging the body and a guided visualization to cleanse the mind and infused steam for the body.
Intention - You will be asked to release what no longer serves you, we will use vocalisation and singing bowls for this process. As well as burning anything written down on paper to be transformed in the fire. Intention in the steam to activate in the space now made.
Grounding - Drum journey and Rain stick to feel the power of Mother Earth whilst immersed in the elemental Sauna.
Protection - Meditation with protective crystals and visualisation to strengthen the energy bodies.
The Fire Pit will be on (Weather permitting) for us to gather and drink tea together whilst sharing the space under the energy and power of the approaching full moon in Gemini.
Victoria’s previous incarnations to the Sauna world were in the areas of intuitive healing. Having trained as an Energy Medicine Practitioner and Sound Therapist.
Victoria regularly held Sound Baths using Gongs and other percussion instruments. She worked intuitively with the frequencies of Crystals and the Subtle energy bodies to effect change in the Human bio-field. This interest and through her profound experiences, led her to the womb-like space of the Sauna environment, naturally aligning with its potential for introspection and transformation.

19:00 21:30
Google Calendar ICS
Join Mythic Sauna this Valentine's and experience a multisensory love story in the wood-fired sauna.
Amberluna Apothecary’s Ellen returns to indulge us. She’ll be weaving her sensory rituals through the romantic love story told by Oliver of Mythic Sauna. The 2.5 hour sauna and storytelling ritual invites you to connect deeply with your body, your self-love and to your open heart.
This won't be some soft-eyed fairytale. Our ancient tale will conjure full-hearted, unreasonable, hopeless, gorgeous romance in all its expansive complexity. We deeply welcome you to come on a date with your gorgeous self, your beloved friend or your smouldering date.
Sensory rituals will build feelings of connectedness and wellbeing with traditional heart-opening and calming herbal teas and encourage sensual body-mind connection with a honey and rose herbal salt scrub. You will enjoy heart-centred aromatherapy throughout, and a final nourishing rosy oil self-massage for the body. We will finish our session with delicious chocolate morsels to replenish our blood sugar and leave our hearts feeling full and our love abundant. Then it's out into the night-time, skin tingling, hearts heated, eyes aglow.
Use code MYTHIC for £5 off your tickets until 07/02/26.

class_type.description:
A two-hour guided experience exploring red light, sauna, and cold to reset the nervous system and deepen recovery.
Begin under BON CHARGE red light masks with breathwork and meditation, before moving into an ARC contrast journey led by ARC Co-founder Alanna - grounded in our signature rituals, somatic guidance, and state-shift sequencing.

We’ll close with an intimate expert panel on red light therapy, contrast, and modern recovery with BON CHARGE founders, ARC Co-founder Alanna, and Dr. Nima, Founder of Remedi London
class_type.name: ARC x BON CHARGE: Light, Heat & Cold

raw.name: ARC x BON CHARGE: Light, Heat & Cold

class_type.description:
A fully guided class in the sauna and ice baths to help you feel present, stable, and connected. 

Connect with breath work, movement, and release pent up energy. Through these integrative practices you’ll ground into the body, find inner stability, and clarity.
class_type.name: Ground - Breathe & ground

class_type.description:
A guided journey through the lounge, sauna, and ice bath chambers, designed to support physical and neurological rewiring. 

This class works with body’s fascial system — the connective tissue network that responds to breath, temperature, nerves, and slow, spiralling movement.

Fascia is deeply connected to the brain and sensory nerves. By moving with awareness, we stimulate neural rewiring, enhancing communication through the body’s natural electrical pathways — fascia, water, and neuro-impulses. Contrast exposure sharpens awareness, boosts adaptability, and creates a clear reset for both body and mind.

Expect to feel more spacious in your body, calm, clear, and grounded in your natural, baseline nervous system. 

No experience needed. Move slowly, feel deeply, let go.
class_type.name: Relax - Letting Go

class_type.description:
A fully guided class in the sauna and ice baths to reset your brain’s reward and satisfaction pathways. 

Through ice baths, breath work, meditation, and mental rewiring, we boost healthy dopamine release, break old habits, and shift your focus to intrinsic motivation. Unlock new levels of growth and peak experiences.
class_type.name: Ground - Dopamine Reset

instructors.bio:
Valentina is a personal development coach, speaker, and thought-leader, also known
as the modern-day guide to limitless living. She partners with peak-performing
individuals and brands in the wellness, entertainment and entrepreneurial space to
help them unlock their full potential.
She takes a holistic and modern approach when it comes to supporting her clients,
which is multifaceted, rooted in spirituality, and backed by science. Valentina has
successfully coached hundreds of clients internationally with her intuitive, empathic
and highly motivating energy and expertise.
instructors.name: Valentina

class_type.description:
Start your day with strength and resilience.

This morning class guided through the sauna and ice bath combines mindfulness, movement, breath work, and visualisation to centre you. Push past limits with sauna and ice baths, building endurance, uncovering your inner strength and reclaiming power.
class_type.name: Energise - Morning Warrior

class_type.description:
A fully guided class inside the sauna and ice baths focusing on to accelerating recovery, enhancing mobility, and preventing injury.

Combining breath work, fascial release, strength work, and lymphatic drainage, this class reduces tension, improves posture, and supports optimal performance. Perfect post-training or after a demanding week, it helps reset your body and keep you moving at your best.
class_type.name: Energise - Stretch & Recover

class_type.description:
A weekly call to step out of the mind and into deeper resonance.
Through functional breathwork and yin-inspired movement, we target the shoulders — a space where we often store tension and emotional weight. Gentle movement and deep breathing create a sense of lightness and ease in the body.
We incorporate the sauna and cold plunges to support nervous system regulation, building resilience and helping the mind settle into presence.
The practice closes with sound therapy using crystal singing bowls — designed to shift brainwaves, promote relaxation, and leave you feeling grounded, clear, and deeply connected.
