raw.level:
Turn up the heat, then cool it right down.

Join us for Sweat & Reset, a high-energy collab between Barry’s and Sauna & Plunge built to push your limits, boost recovery, and bring our wellness community together.

Event Schedule

🕠 4.15pm – 5.15pm · Barry’s East Class
Meet at Barry's East for a start strong with the iconic Red Room sweat session.

🕡 5.15pm – 5.45pm · Shake & Stroll
Refuel with a Barrys shake and walk round the corner with the crew.

🕖 5.45pm – 6.45pm · Contrast Therapy & Social
Reset with hot Finnish and infrared saunas and cold plunges at 3°, 6°, and 9°, then unwind with drinks, chats, and good vibes.

🕖 6.45pm - 7.00pm · Close

Sweat hard. Recover deeper. Connect stronger.

Limited spots available, an social evening of movement, recovery, and community.

🔥 Secure your spot. Sweat. Reset. Repeat!

A Galentine’s wellness social designed to slow down together. Gather with your girls for sauna and cold plunge rituals, intention setting, and feel-good moments of connection. Come as you are, laugh, unwind, and leave feeling deeply refreshed, supported, and celebrated- by yourself and by each other.

6:00 – 6:15 | Welcome
Arrive, exhale. Soft music, warm lighting, robes, towels, and a hydration station set the tone. You’ll receive an intention card and journal to guide your evening.

6:15 – 7:00 | Sauna & Plunge Ritual
A guided ritual, not a challenge. Gentle breath cues, soundbath music, and full permission to move, pause, or opt out as your body needs.

7:00 – 7:15 | Connection
Rest and reconnect in our Dry Off space with blankets, hydration, and light snacks.

7:15 – 7:45 | Studio
Settle into a 30-minute restorative and meditative studio session to calm your nervous system.

7:45 – 8:15 | Connection & Intention
Reflect in your journal, capture what surfaced, and set an intention to carry forward. We close with a grounding moment together.

Each guest leaves with a small grounding token (journal & tote) to take the experience with you.

EARLY BIRD: 0-4 Tickets - £30 
STANDARD: 5-8 Tickets - £40
FINAL TICKETS: 9-12 Tickets - £50

events.event_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.session_name: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai

raw.sessionName: Galentines Guided Banya with Sasha Davai
raw.level:
Join us for a very special Galentines banya with Sasha Davai. 

Banya is a traditional Slavic bathing practice, similar to a sauna, but with slightly lower heat and higher humidity, designed to soften the body and deepen the effects of steam.

The session unfolds over two to three guided steam cycles and includes special herbal steam inhalations, honey and salt scrubs, oak-leaf whisking, and cooling ice massage. We'll also drink specially brewed tea. 

Each element is introduced gently, allowing time for rest, integration, and connection.

This session is ideal if you:

Are curious about banya or guided sauna rituals

Enjoy sensory, ritual-led experiences

Want something nurturing, grounding, and communal

Are looking for a slower, more intentional sauna experience

Join us for a unique evening combining the joy of singing with the relaxation of sauna. 

This special session brings together sauna ritual and singing meditation - two powerful practices for grounding the body, calming the nervous system, and creating connection.

We’ll begin with 40 minutes in the sauna, allowing heat, steam and stillness to help you soften, slow down, and arrive fully in your body. After cooling and settling, we’ll transition into 40 minutes of Singing Meditation, led live from the keyboard by Jacob, founder of Singing Meditation.

Jacob is a professional musician and daily meditator who discovered that singing can be one of the most accessible ways to deepen presence and focus - no prior meditation or musical experience required.

Using a simple call-and-response format, Jacob guides the group through gentle songs and mantras, building two- and three-part harmonies organically. There’s no sheet music, no pressure, and no “right” way to participate. You’re invited to:

Sing the main melody
Explore harmonies or improvisation
Or simply listen and absorb the sound

At the heart of this session is choice, accessibility, and shared calm. Whether you sing or stay quiet, sound becomes a meditative tool, something you can lean into, rather than perform.

This is a warm, inclusive space designed to help you drop out of your head, reconnect with your breath, and experience rest through rhythm and resonance.

No singing experience needed.
Just come as you are.

email_candidates.title: Skuna Boats is promoting Valentine's Day bookings for hot tub boat cruises and igloo boats at West I
email_candidates.summary:
Here are the key points extracted from the Skuna Boats newsletter:

*   **Valentine’s Day & February Bookings:** Skuna Boats is promoting date night experiences throughout February at their **West India Quay** location in London.
*   **Hot Tub Boat Experiences:** Heated boat cruises are available for couples or groups, featuring a range of drinks available for purchase while sailing.
*   **Igloo Boat Hire:** Private, enclosed "Igloo Boats" are available for daytime or evening cruises, featuring decorative lighting and fondue dining options.
*   **Booking Recommendation:** Due to high demand for Valentine's Day, customers are advised to book in advance via their website to secure specific time slots.

email_candidates.summary:
Here are the key points from the Yard Sauna update:

*   **Opening Date:** Yard Sauna is now scheduled to officially open in February to allow for final site logistics and finishing touches.
*   **Construction Status:** The build is nearing completion, with final preparations currently underway.
*   **Bookings:** Booking details and the reservation calendar will be released soon.
*   **Priority Access:** Early subscribers will be the first to receive notification when the booking system goes live.
*   **Contact Info:** Inquiries can be directed to yardsauna@outlook.com or through their website at www.yardsauna.co.uk.

email_candidates.title: Updates on London community sauna locations including the Peckham re-opening, new session schedules,
email_candidates.summary:
Here are the key takeaways from the newsletter:

*   **Peckham Re-opening:** The Glengall Wharf Community Garden site reopens on January 23rd. It will operate Fridays–Sundays during daylight hours with a simplified, off-grid setup (saunas and showers only, no plunges) and reduced ticket prices.
*   **Schedule Updates (Walthamstow & Camberwell):** Starting January 30th, rolling 1-hour sessions will be introduced at Walthamstow (Fridays, 7:00 AM – 12:00 PM) and Camberwell (Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays, 7:00 AM – 12:00 PM).
*   **Stratford FLINTA Session Change:** Beginning February 4th, the FLINTA session is moving from Thursday evenings to Wednesday evenings. The time remains 8:30 PM.
*   **Hackney Wick Event:** On Monday, February 17th, there will be a presentation on cold-water immersion research at 1:30 PM, followed by the 2:00 PM sauna session.
*   **Promotion & Recruitment:** The sauna is running a haiku contest to promote the launch of "Bum Towels" (entries to emily@community-sauna.co.uk) and is currently hiring an Operations Manager.
*   **Camberwell Closure:** The Camberwell site will be closing briefly for maintenance/TLC (specific dates were cut off in the announcement).
